# Fallback identities for git over SSH.
#
# github.com and ddoghq.github.com are pinned by the managed git-config-tool
# config to its ghkeys with `IdentitiesOnly yes`, and those private keys live on
# the laptop — they reach the workspace only through the forwarded agent, which
# dies when the laptop sleeps. `IdentityFile` is additive, so naming our on-disk
# keys here appends them to each host's identity list (IdentitiesOnly still
# holds). This file is included before the managed config, so our keys are
# offered first; since each host maps to exactly one account there is no
# wrong-account risk:
#   github.com        -> tausman             (id_ed25519_tausman)
#   ddoghq.github.com -> tausif-rahman_ddog  (id_ed25519_ddog)
#
# The keypairs are generated per-workstation by install.sh and are never
# committed; only this static reference is version-controlled. Each key must be
# SSO-authorized for its org (install.sh walks you through this).
Host github.com
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_tausman

Host ddoghq.github.com
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_ddog
